meanings.definition: To surpass in humor or wit.
meanings.sent1: She outhumored her friends with her clever jokes.
meanings.sent2: He always tries to outhumor his classmates during lunchtime.
meanings.sent3: The comedian outhumored the audience with his hilarious stand-up routine.
meanings.sent4: Her quick wit outhumored everyone in the room.
meanings.sent5: The comedy show outhumored all other performances at the festival.

meanings.definition: To be more humorous or witty than someone else.
meanings.sent1: They outhumored their rivals with their funny skit.
meanings.sent2: The siblings constantly try to outhumor each other at family gatherings.
meanings.sent3: The playful banter between friends often leads to outhumoring one another.
meanings.sent4: His clever retort outhumored his opponent in the debate.
meanings.sent5: The comedy duo always manages to outhumor the audience with their hilarious sketches.
